----------------
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN CONSTRUCTOR AND PROTOTYPE

Every object's (Ex: obj1) prototype has a property called 'constructor' which is the
created object(obj1) itself and it will be called automatically when a new object (Ex: obj2) is created is
created out of (obj1)